title: For Sale/Trade:  Siamese Mauser in 45-70
location: Sold to a buyer in Texas, Columbus, Ohio
postcontent:
This gun is presently up on Gunbroker for $950 Buy It Now. The auction ends this evening. There is no reserve and someone has bid on it. Any way you look at it, the opportunity to buy this rifle ends tonight. If you're serious about it, don't wait. 

I have the pleasure of offering a nice Bolt Action Mauser in 45-70 for sale or trade!
It will take down any animal in North America, up through the largest of dangerous game.  This cartrige has been used to take down elephants and cape buffalo. In this action the cartridge can be loaded up to .458 Win Mag equivalence.

If you want to go to the range and have The Biggest Gun (unless somebody shows up with a .50 BMG), this is the gun for you.

The cartrige has been around for almost 150 years.  It is fired from a German designed action.  All it needs is your scope & rings.  The sasety is simple to operate and verify the setting (The Mauser was, after all, a military weapon, so it had to be GI proof).

This Gun:
It is ready for your choice of scope and rings.  The stock is good looking, but has the occasional dent and scratch.  I have LOTS of photos that include the little details and things.  I will happily e-mail them to potential buyers.  (I can only post three here)  It has a good recoil pad.  The bolt locks up tight, but works easily.   And the Trigger.  The trigger is Niiiiiice!  Disengage the safety, line up your shot and make the decision to fire and it's Gone!  You won't miss a shot because the trigger is too heavy or creepy.  

Whether you want to have The Big Gun at the range or have the right gun to protect yourself from the bear or moose that decided you're too close, this gun will Do The Job.  It isn't a super shiny, pretty gun.  It sends heavy bullets out of itself and makes Big, Big holes.

I live in Ohio and can do business face to face with other Ohio residents.  Seeing an CCW card is reassuring, but seeing your driver's license well enough to verify that you're from Ohio is also sufficient for this transaction. You will also be asked to reassure me that there is no reason that would prevent you from buying a firearm, legally.  As this rifle is rather pricey, I am willing to travel within the state for the right deal.  The price is absolutely negotiable.  Make an offer and it'll open a dialogue.  Maybe it'll end up with you buying a cool and unique rifle.

If you live outside Ohio, I can ship to your FFL  by one of two methods.
1: If your FFL will accept shipment from individuals, I will ship to the shop at cost estimated by the UPS website (dimensions and weight and sufficient insurance).
2: I will take it to my FFL to be shipped to your FFL for what my FFL charges.

Payment will be something we'll have to sort out when all of the other details are resolved.  It's a lot of money and it's important for everybody to have their assets protected.  Postal money orders are nice and allow the buyer the recourse of the postal service if there are issues with the transaction.

It's up as an auction on Gunbroker, so one way or another, it's going to sell.  Don't wait.  It will get away and you'll be left with alternatives that aren't as nice and/or cost more.

Picture Collectors: By all means, drop me a note. Sending e-mail is free and this gun is relatively unique. I'll be happy to send photos even if you have no intention of bidding.

The 5.7mm cartridge was designed to perform optimally out of a shorter barrel and generates velocities so high that several loadings are available that are classified as armor piercing. For these reasons the 5.7mm cartridge faithfully serves the US Secret Service in protecting some of our nations most influential people. While the Five-seveN® is available in several different configurations the model that you are bidding on has adjustable sights that can be adjusted for both windage and elevation.
